                    <div class="temp-label" style="bottom: 50px; right: 30px;">Cool Air Enters</div>
                    <div style="position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); 
                                background: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 28px;">
                        ΔT drives flow
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 30px; font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.6;">
                <strong>Key Principle:</strong> 10°C difference = 3.5 Pa pressure difference<br>
                <strong>Height Factor:</strong> Every 3m of height doubles the effect
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="flex: 1;">
            <h2>Night Purge Strategy</h2>

            <div class="content-box">
                <h3 style="color: #2c5aa0; margin-bottom: 20px;">When Outside < 26°C:</h3>
                <ol style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.8;">
                    <li><strong>10 PM:</strong> Open high windows (top floor/roof)</li>
                    <li><strong>10:15 PM:</strong> Open low windows (ground floor)</li>
                    <li><strong>All Night:</strong> Let thermal mass cool down</li>
                    <li><strong>6 AM:</strong> Close all openings before heat returns</li>
                </ol>

                <div style="margin-top: 30px; padding: 20px; background: #e7f3ff; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <strong>Result:</strong> Interior stays 3-5°C cooler until noon<br>
                    <strong>Cost:</strong> Zero IQD - just smart timing
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="warning-box" style="margin-top: 30px;">
        <span class="warning-icon">⚠️</span>
        <strong>Security Note:</strong> Install mesh screens or security bars that still allow airflow. 
        Consider automated louvers for upper windows if security is a concern.
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <span>Towards decent and affordable housing in Iraq</span>
    </div>
</div>

